Exxon Mobil Corp To Buy Celtic Exploration Ltd.-DJ
Wednesday, 17 Oct 2012 07:55am EDT
Dow Jones reported that Exxon Mobil Corp agreed to buy Celtic Exploration Ltd. in a deal worth about CDN$3.1 billion ($3.14 billion), including debt. Celtic said Exxon Mobil's Canadian unit is offering CDN$24.50 a share for its outstanding shares, plus 0.5 of a share of a new company, representing a 35% premium to Celtic's closing price of CDN$18.12 in Toronto Tuesday. The deal, which includes a CDN$90 million break-up fee payable under certain circumstances by Celtic, is subject to Celtic shareholder approval and approval by Canadian regulators.Â 
